description:
Infrared Roses is a live compilation album by the Grateful Dead. It is a conglomeration of their famous improvisational segments &quot;Drums&quot; and &quot;Space.&quot;

Somewhere in the middle of the second set of a Grateful Dead concert came a period of musical improvisation. This part of the concert is commonly referred to as &quot;Space,&quot; and came right after a drum solo or duet. Infrared Roses is a compilation of these performances. There are no recognizable songs from the band&amp;#039;s repertoire on this release. Robert Hunter, probably best known for his numerous collaborations with the Grateful Dead, created the names of the tracks for the album.

